<li id="cite_note-113"><b><a href="#cite_ref-113" title="">^</a></b> V.D. Savarkar argues that the rebellion was a war of Indian independence. <i>The Indian War of Independence: 1857</i> (Bombay: 1947 [1909]). Most historians have seen his arguments as discredited, with one venturing so far as to say, 'It was neither first, nor national, nor a war of independence.' Eric Stokes has argued that the rebellion was actually a variety of movements, not one movement. <i>The Peasant Armed</i> (Oxford: 1980). See also S.B. Chaudhuri, <i>Civil Rebellion in the Indian Mutinies 1857-1859" (Calcutta: 1957)</i></li>
